#+
# Name:
#    _GET_SATURATION_LEVEL_
#
# Purpose:
#    Finds the ClassicCam saturation level in ADU the current Frame.
#
# Language:
#    Perl5
#
# Description:
#    This primitive obtains the ClassicCam saturation level in ADU for the current
#    frame.
#
#    The saturation level is returned through an argument.
#
# Arguments:
#    SATURATION = REAL (Returned)
#       The saturation level obtained.
#
# Notes:
#    -  This primitive is only suitable for ClassicCam.
#    -  The values are taken from the instrument's Web page, viz.
#    http://www.ociw.edu/magellan_lco/instruments/Classic_Cam/manual.html.
#
# Authors:
#    MJC: Malcolm J. Currie (Starlink)
#
# Copyright:
#    Copyright (C) 2003 Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
#    Council.  All Rights Reserved.
#
#-

# Just use a single default for now.
    my $saturation = 16000;
    $_GET_SATURATION_LEVEL_{SATURATION} = $saturation;

# Podule
# ======

=head1 NAME

_GET_SATURATION_LEVEL_ -- Finds the ClassicCam saturation level in ADU the current Frame.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This primitive obtains the ClassicCam saturation level in ADU for the current
frame.

The saturation level is returned through an argument.

=head1 ARGUMENTS

=over 4

=item SATURATION = REAL (Returned)

The saturation level obtained.

=back

=head1 NOTES

=over 4

=item *

This primitive is only suitable for ClassicCam.

=item *

The values are taken from the instrument's Web page, viz.
L<http://www.ociw.edu/magellan_lco/instruments/Classic_Cam/manual.html|http://www.ociw.edu/magellan_lco/instruments/Classic_Cam/manual.html>.

=back

=head1 AUTHORS

MJC: Malcolm J. Currie (Starlink)

=head1 COPYRIGHT

